JOHANNESBURG – One ranger was killed during the kidnapping of two British tourists in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). Soldiers have been deployed and park rangers launched an operation to find the two tourists who were ambushed by armed men at the Virunga National Park. BREAKING I now have it confirmed that two British tourists, one man and one woman, kidnapped in Democratic Republic of Congo.....local reports say ambushed by bandits now demanding ransom of $200,000 Eastern Congo has been the scene of successive waves of violence in recent decades. READ: 17 deaths reported in DRC as Ebola outbreak confirmed Rebel groups and militias still control large swathes of the territory. Nearly 200 rangers have died protecting the park in recent years. eNCA